Step 1. Calculate the Quick Assets. Quick assets include Cash on Hand, Bank Deposits, Accounts Receivable, and Interest Receivable. From the balance sheet, their End_amount values are:  
 • Cash on Hand = 5,603,438.00  
 • Bank Deposits = 3,642,142.45  
 • Interest Receivable = 10,710.07  
 • Accounts Receivable = 1,355,463.34  

Sum of Quick Assets = 5,603,438.00 + 3,642,142.45 + 1,355,463.34 + 10,710.07 = 10,611,753.86

Step 2. Total Current Liabilities is given as 2,110,671.05.  
Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities = 10,611,753.86 / 2,110,671.05 ≈ 5.03

Step 3. Calculate Net Profit Margin. From the income statement:  
 • Net Profit = 1,103,190.60  
 • Total Revenue = 5,813,420.67  
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
 = (1,103,190.60 / 5,813,420.67) × 100% ≈ 18.97%

Thus, the solution in the required format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "5.03",
    "Net Profit Margin": "18.97%"
  }
}
